Processing Data

1. Vaccine Data

country_vaccinations_df = read_csv("data/country_vaccinations.csv") %>% 
  drop_na(daily_vaccinations, daily_vaccinations_per_million) %>% 
  mutate(date_month_string = str_sub(date, 1, 7)) %>% 
  group_by(country,date_month_string) %>% 
  summarise(
    monthly_vaccinations_per_country = sum(daily_vaccinations),
    monthly_vaccinations_per_million_per_country = sum(daily_vaccinations_per_million)
  ) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  mutate(date_month_number = as.numeric(str_sub(date_month_string, 4, 4)) * 12 +
                             as.numeric(str_sub(date_month_string, 6, 7)) - 11) %>% 
  group_by(date_month_string) %>% 
  mutate(
#   monthly_vaccinations_per_million_globally = sum(monthly_vaccinations_per_million_per_country),
    monthly_vaccinations_globally = sum(monthly_vaccinations_per_country)
  )

2. Twitter Data

compound_0_df = read_csv("data/whole_clean_df.csv") %>% 
  rename(country = Country) %>% 
  drop_na(compound) %>% 
  mutate(date_month_string = str_sub(date, 1, 7)) %>% 
  group_by(country,date_month_string) %>% 
  summarise(
    positive_per_country = sum(compound > 0),
    neutral_per_country = sum(compound == 0),
    negative_per_country = sum(compound < 0),
    positive_rate_per_country = positive_per_country / (positive_per_country + neutral_per_country + negative_per_country),
    neutral_rate_per_country = neutral_per_country / (positive_per_country + neutral_per_country + negative_per_country),
    negative_rate_per_country = negative_per_country / (positive_per_country + neutral_per_country + negative_per_country)
  ) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  mutate(date_month_number = as.numeric(str_sub(date_month_string, 4, 4)) * 12 +
                             as.numeric(str_sub(date_month_string, 6, 7)) - 11) %>% 
  group_by(date_month_string) %>% 
  mutate(
    positive_globally = sum(positive_per_country),
    neutral_globally = sum(neutral_per_country),
    negative_globally = sum(negative_per_country),
    positive_rate_globally = positive_globally / (positive_globally + neutral_globally + negative_globally),
    neutral_rate_globally = neutral_globally / (positive_globally + neutral_globally + negative_globally),
    negative_rate_globally = negative_globally / (positive_globally + neutral_globally + negative_globally)
  )

1.0 monthly_vaccinations_globally trend for all countries. [Significant]

vaccinations_df = country_vaccinations_df

  ggplot(aes(x = date_month_string, y = monthly_vaccinations_globally)) +
  geom_point(color = "blue") +
